WEBVTT

00:02.068 --> 00:03.296
To me, government...

00:04.871 --> 00:06.566
...is basically parents for adults.

00:07.207 --> 00:10.404
Especially the IRS. The IRS is like
Ward and June Cleaver...

00:11.011 --> 00:13.605
...and we're all
Wally and the Beaver.

00:13.780 --> 00:15.645
And your accountant
is Eddie Haskell...

00:15.815 --> 00:18.511
...showing you all these neat tricks
to get away with stuff.

00:19.252 --> 00:20.844
That's fine, unless you get audited.

00:21.021 --> 00:23.546
Then you don't want some
wise guy in a suit going:

00:23.723 --> 00:27.022
"You have a very
lovely office here, sir."

00:27.260 --> 00:30.525
Because jail is the government's
way of sending you to your room.

00:30.697 --> 00:34.133
And when you meet Whitey
and Lumpy in the joint...

00:34.968 --> 00:38.199
...there's really gonna be
something wrong with the Beaver.

00:44.210 --> 00:45.871
-Does he like you?
-What do you think?

00:46.046 --> 00:48.173
-Do you like him?
-Yeah, I like him. Definitely.

00:48.348 --> 00:49.576
I like him a lot.

00:49.749 --> 00:52.309
-So, what's wrong with him?
-Nothing, and I've looked.

00:52.485 --> 00:54.749
Well, I'm sure you'll find something.

00:54.921 --> 00:56.718
-So how'd you meet him?
-In the office.

00:56.890 --> 00:58.721
-So he's a writer?
-Yeah.

00:58.892 --> 01:01.690
-Yeah, big surprise.
-I was sitting on the reception desk.

01:01.861 --> 01:03.920
I was looking pretty hot.

01:04.096 --> 01:06.964
-I was wearing my slingback pumps.
-What are those?

01:07.133 --> 01:09.897
Ask your mother.
You live with her now, don't you?

01:10.603 --> 01:12.127
Anyway...

01:12.305 --> 01:15.297
...then this guy comes up to me,
and he starts feeling my jacket...

01:15.475 --> 01:17.966
...between his thumb
and forefinger like this.

01:18.144 --> 01:20.544
-So, what'd you do?
-I said, "What do you think?"

01:20.713 --> 01:22.203
And he said, "Gabardine?"

01:22.382 --> 01:25.249
And I said, "Yeah." That was it.

01:27.187 --> 01:30.054
-Just felt your material?
-Yeah. Jake Jarmel.

01:30.757 --> 01:33.021
-Sounds like a cool guy.
-Sounds like a jerk.

01:33.193 --> 01:35.923
Felt your material, come on.

01:36.096 --> 01:39.031
-Jerry, where'd you get that sweater?
-In the back of my closet.

01:39.199 --> 01:42.168
I think that's what the back
of closets are for.

01:43.169 --> 01:44.659
Hey, that's Barry.

01:44.838 --> 01:46.362
Lookit. Barry.

01:46.606 --> 01:48.073
-Hey.
-Hi.

01:48.241 --> 01:50.971
-Who is that?
-That's Barry Prophet, our accountant.

01:51.144 --> 01:53.612
I don't know how can you let
this guy handle your money.

01:53.780 --> 01:56.806
Not my money. He handles
Jerry's money. He just does my taxes.

01:56.983 --> 01:58.541
-Barry, how you doing?
-How are you?

01:58.718 --> 02:00.117
-This is my friend George.
-Hey.

02:00.286 --> 02:02.083
What are you doing
in this neighborhood?

02:02.255 --> 02:03.779
Nothing, really.

02:04.424 --> 02:06.551
-You... You eat here?
-Yeah.

02:06.726 --> 02:09.455
-So how's my money?
-Well, it's still green.

02:09.628 --> 02:11.529
-What, do you got a cold?
-No. No.

02:12.232 --> 02:15.633
-Look at that ring.
-Oh, you like that?

02:17.504 --> 02:18.994
Hey, say, where's the bathroom?

02:19.172 --> 02:21.163
Bathroom?
Bathroom's right over there.

02:21.341 --> 02:23.036
Great.

02:24.911 --> 02:26.139
Did you see that?

02:26.312 --> 02:28.177
-See what?
-Yes, I saw that.

02:28.348 --> 02:30.316
-What?
-What was all that sniffing?

02:30.483 --> 02:32.576
-I don't know.
-You don't think..?

02:32.752 --> 02:35.118
Oh, no. Come on, Jerry.

02:35.288 --> 02:37.916
He was definitely sniffing.

02:38.858 --> 02:41.326
I mean, what if..?
This guy's got all my money.

02:41.494 --> 02:43.428
Plus, I got some of Kramer's money
with him.

02:43.596 --> 02:45.723
He can write checks to himself
from my account.

02:45.899 --> 02:48.367
I've known this guy since college.
He doesn't do drugs.

02:48.535 --> 02:51.663
-Then what was all that sniffing?
-Maybe it's the cold weather.

02:51.838 --> 02:53.237
Today's not cold.

02:53.406 --> 02:56.432
All right, I gotta get going.
My parents are expecting me.

02:56.609 --> 03:00.340
Don't forget to wash
your hands before supper.

03:05.518 --> 03:07.952
What do you need
all that ketchup for?

03:09.556 --> 03:11.683
This is my ketchup.

03:12.091 --> 03:13.456
I bought this ketchup...

03:13.626 --> 03:16.652
...just so I could have
as much as I want.

03:19.098 --> 03:22.363
So I...
I talked to Phil Kassikoff today.

03:22.535 --> 03:24.059
Phil Kassikoff?

03:24.237 --> 03:26.398
Yeah. You know, my friend,
the bra salesman?

03:26.940 --> 03:28.874
He says they're looking
for somebody...

03:29.042 --> 03:31.602
...so I got you an interview
next Friday with his boss.

03:31.778 --> 03:33.871
-Next Friday? What time?
-Two o'clock.

03:34.447 --> 03:37.814
That's my whole afternoon.
I was gonna look for sneakers.

03:37.984 --> 03:39.952
You can look for sneakers
the next day!

03:41.554 --> 03:44.148
He doesn't know anything
about bras.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.161
I know a little.

03:49.762 --> 03:51.559
Besides, what do you
have to know?

03:51.731 --> 03:55.997
Well, it wouldn't hurt to go in
and be able to discuss it intelligently.

03:56.169 --> 03:58.296
Maybe you should take a look
at a few bras.

03:58.471 --> 04:00.405
Where's your bra?
Give him a bra to look at.

04:00.573 --> 04:02.006
I'm not giving him a bra.

04:02.175 --> 04:05.338
-Why not?
-I don't need him looking at my bra.

04:05.511 --> 04:07.172
Fine. He'll go into the interview...

04:07.347 --> 04:09.372
...he wouldn't know
what he's talking about.

04:09.549 --> 04:11.312
Do we have to..?

04:11.484 --> 04:13.543
You don't even know
what they're made from.

04:13.720 --> 04:17.247
-They're made from Lycra spandex.
-Get out of here. Lycra spandex?

04:17.423 --> 04:19.721
I think they are made
from Lycra spandex.

04:19.892 --> 04:21.791
-Wanna bet? How much?
-I'm not betting.

04:21.961 --> 04:25.863
-Take a look.
-All right, I'll get a bra.

04:26.032 --> 04:28.899
I don't know what the big problem is
getting a bra.

04:29.068 --> 04:30.592
She doesn't wanna get a bra.

04:31.070 --> 04:33.664
I'm not saying, "Go to the library
and read the history."

04:33.840 --> 04:36.741
But it wouldn't kill you
to know a little bit about it.

04:36.909 --> 04:39.070
All right, it wouldn't kill me.

04:42.181 --> 04:44.149
How long does it take to find a bra?

04:44.550 --> 04:46.211
What's going on in there?

04:46.386 --> 04:49.685
You ask me to get a pair of
underwear, I'm back in two seconds.

04:51.024 --> 04:53.618
You know about the cup sizes
and all?

04:55.795 --> 05:00.164
-They have different cups.
-Yeah, I know about the cups.

05:03.236 --> 05:05.170
You got the A...

05:05.838 --> 05:07.169
...the B...

05:07.340 --> 05:08.898
...the C...

05:09.309 --> 05:11.743
...the D. That's the biggest.

05:12.979 --> 05:14.879
I know the D is the biggest.

05:15.048 --> 05:18.814
I base my whole life on knowing
that the D is the biggest.

05:18.985 --> 05:21.283
-Here. Here's the bra.
-Let me see it.

05:21.454 --> 05:23.979
"One hundred percent
Lycra spandex."

05:24.157 --> 05:26.148
-Let me see.
-I told you.

05:26.326 --> 05:29.557
Here. You think you know
everything.

05:31.130 --> 05:32.757
That's surprising.

05:33.433 --> 05:35.094
All right, what else?

05:35.268 --> 05:37.600
You got the cups in the front...

05:37.770 --> 05:40.432
...two loops in the back, all right?

05:40.606 --> 05:44.167
-I guess that's about it.
-I got it. Cups in front, loops in back.

05:44.344 --> 05:46.778
You got ketchup on it.

05:53.252 --> 05:55.220
Sniffing? What do you mean,
sniffing?

05:55.388 --> 05:58.516
-Sniffing. With his nose.
-Jerry, he probably had a cold.

05:58.691 --> 06:01.660
-No, he didn't. I asked him.
-So, what are you saying?

06:01.828 --> 06:05.025
-I don't know. You know, what if..?
-Drugs?

06:05.198 --> 06:07.393
-You think he's on drugs?
-I don't know.

06:07.567 --> 06:09.296
-Jerry...
-All I know is he was sniffing.

06:09.469 --> 06:11.596
-Listen, we went in on a CD together.
-I know.

06:11.771 --> 06:13.238
And Newman gave you money too.

06:13.406 --> 06:16.000
See, I didn't even meet this guy.
We trusted you.

06:16.175 --> 06:18.405
Look, it doesn't necessarily
mean anything yet.

06:18.578 --> 06:21.479
-It just means he was sniffing.
-Well, what else? Was he nervous?

06:21.647 --> 06:25.413
Did he use a lot of slang?
Did he use the word "man"?

06:27.520 --> 06:28.885
No, he didn't use "man."

06:29.055 --> 06:32.081
I mean, when he was leaving,
did he say, "I'm splitting"?

06:32.959 --> 06:35.427
No, but at one point,
he did use the bathroom.

06:39.665 --> 06:42.293
-You think that's a bad sign?
-Yes, that's what they do.

06:42.468 --> 06:43.935
They live in the bathroom.

06:44.103 --> 06:46.571
What are we gonna do?
We're gonna get our money, right?

06:46.739 --> 06:48.673
I don't know.
This sweater really itches me.

06:48.841 --> 06:50.570
-You want it?
-Yeah.

06:55.248 --> 06:57.910
Hello. Hel...

06:59.018 --> 07:00.815
Well, you notice anything?

07:00.987 --> 07:03.581
You have cleaned up
the whole apartment...

07:03.756 --> 07:05.690
...and you're making dinner.
You're perfect.

07:05.858 --> 07:08.418
You're a perfect man.

07:12.932 --> 07:14.900
-Did anyone call?
-You got a few messages.

07:15.067 --> 07:16.864
-I wrote them down.
-Where are they?

07:17.036 --> 07:20.472
Let's see, they are...
Here they are.

07:20.640 --> 07:22.574
Thank you.

07:22.742 --> 07:25.404
Oh, yeah. I'll call you back.

07:26.813 --> 07:29.714
Forget that...
Myra had the baby!

07:29.882 --> 07:31.509
Oh, my God. That's wonderful.

07:31.684 --> 07:33.015
-Who called?
-She did.

07:33.186 --> 07:35.518
She did? Oh, that's so great.

07:35.955 --> 07:39.220
-Where do you keep the corkscrew?
-It's in the drawer on the right.

07:43.362 --> 07:44.795
What?

07:44.997 --> 07:46.555
No, it's nothing.

07:46.732 --> 07:48.962
-No, what is it?
-It's nothing.

07:49.235 --> 07:50.725
Tell me.

07:51.270 --> 07:55.832
Well, I was just curious why you
didn't use an exclamation point.

07:58.311 --> 07:59.573
What are you talking about?

07:59.745 --> 08:02.077
Well, see right here? You wrote,
"Myra had the baby."

08:02.248 --> 08:05.046
But you didn't use
an exclamation point.

08:05.218 --> 08:06.810
So?

08:06.986 --> 08:09.477
So it's... Yeah, it's nothing.
Forget it. Forget it.

08:09.655 --> 08:11.623
You know, I just found it curious.

08:11.791 --> 08:14.453
Wait, what's so curious about it?

08:14.627 --> 08:18.563
Well, I mean, if one of your
close friends had a baby...

08:18.731 --> 08:21.996
...and I left you a message about it,
I would use an exclamation point.

08:22.168 --> 08:24.295
Well, maybe I don't use
my exclamation points...

08:24.470 --> 08:26.597
...as haphazardly as you do.

08:27.573 --> 08:30.269
You don't think
that someone having a baby...

08:30.443 --> 08:32.274
...warrants an exclamation point?

08:32.445 --> 08:34.379
Hey, look, I just jotted down
the message.

08:34.547 --> 08:37.914
I didn't know that I was required
to capture the mood of each caller.

08:38.251 --> 08:42.482
Well, I just thought you'd be a little
more excited about a friend of mine...

08:42.655 --> 08:44.623
...having a baby.
-Okay, I'm excited.

08:44.790 --> 08:47.122
I just don't happen to like
exclamation points.

08:47.293 --> 08:49.284
Well, Jake, you should
learn to use them.

08:49.462 --> 08:52.329
Like, the way I'm talking now,
I'd put exclamation points...

08:52.498 --> 08:55.990
...on the ends all of these sentences!
On this one! And on that one!

08:56.168 --> 08:58.500
Well, you can put one on this one:

08:58.671 --> 09:00.195
I'm leaving!

09:05.578 --> 09:07.375
-You're out of your mind.
-Why?

09:07.547 --> 09:09.481
It's an exclamation point.

09:09.649 --> 09:13.278
-It's a line with a dot under it.
-Well, I felt it called for one.

09:13.452 --> 09:15.750
"Called for one." I thought
I'd heard of everything.

09:15.922 --> 09:18.914
I never heard of a relationship
being affected by punctuation.

09:19.091 --> 09:21.753
I found it very troubling
that he didn't use one.

09:23.062 --> 09:25.724
George is right.
Didn't take you long.

09:29.302 --> 09:31.236
Anything new with that guy
on drugs?

09:31.671 --> 09:33.263
He's not on drugs.

09:33.439 --> 09:37.500
Then why the sniffing?
Who walks around... sniffing?

09:37.677 --> 09:39.770
All right, here.
You call him right now, okay?

09:39.946 --> 09:43.177
-See if he's sniffing right now.
-Good idea.

09:47.687 --> 09:50.520
-<i>Prophet and Goldstein.</i>
-Yes, Barry Prophet, please.

09:50.690 --> 09:52.521
<i>I'm sorry, he's out of town
this week.</i>

09:52.692 --> 09:55.252
-Out of town?
-<i>Yes. He went to South America.</i>

09:55.428 --> 09:57.919
-South America?
-South America?

09:58.097 --> 09:59.758
I'll call back. Thank you.

09:59.932 --> 10:03.026
-He went to South America.
-Yeah!

10:04.003 --> 10:05.436
So what?

10:05.771 --> 10:09.673
-Who goes to South America?
-People go to South America.

10:09.842 --> 10:13.141
Yeah, and they come back with
things taped to their large intestine.

10:14.046 --> 10:15.775
So because of a few bad apples...

10:15.948 --> 10:18.143
...you're gonna impugn
an entire continent?

10:18.317 --> 10:20.217
Yes, I'm impugning a continent.

10:20.386 --> 10:22.786
Well, I say we go and get
our money right now.

10:23.255 --> 10:26.122
-Hey. Hey.
-Hello, Newman.

10:26.292 --> 10:28.283
Hello, Jerry.

10:28.628 --> 10:29.993
So any news?

10:30.162 --> 10:32.323
Yeah, he skipped out
and... went to South America.

10:32.498 --> 10:33.726
South America?!

10:33.899 --> 10:37.164
What kind of snow blower
did you get us mixed up with?

10:37.637 --> 10:41.437
Okay, gentlemen, the fact remains
you still have no proof.

10:41.607 --> 10:43.905
This is all speculation and hearsay.

10:44.076 --> 10:47.341
Wait. There's one way to find out.
We set up a sting.

10:48.080 --> 10:51.777
You know, like Abscam.
Like Abscam, Jerry.

10:52.385 --> 10:53.613
What are you gonna do?

10:53.786 --> 10:57.187
You gonna put on phony beards
and dress up like Arab sheiks...

10:57.356 --> 10:59.119
...and sit around
in some hotel room?

10:59.291 --> 11:01.691
-I mean, come on.
-Wait a second.

11:01.861 --> 11:04.022
Maybe there is a way to tempt him
and find out.

11:04.196 --> 11:08.257
If we put our three heads together,
we should come up with something.

