contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

11:17.677 --> 11:20.441
-What's today?
-It's Thursday.

11:20.613 --> 11:22.012
Really?

11:22.181 --> 11:24.274
Feels like Tuesday.

11:24.917 --> 11:26.817
Tuesday has no feel.

11:26.986 --> 11:29.147
Monday has a feel.

11:29.355 --> 11:31.050
Friday has a feel.

11:31.223 --> 11:32.451
Sunday has a feel.

11:32.625 --> 11:35.458
-I feel Tuesday and Wednesday.
-Shut up, the both of you.

11:35.628 --> 11:36.959
You're making me nervous.

11:38.064 --> 11:40.965
Where is he already? He should've
been out of work by now.

11:41.133 --> 11:42.532
Hey, this is kind of fun.

11:42.702 --> 11:45.398
Yeah. Maybe we ought to become
private detectives.

11:45.571 --> 11:46.970
Yeah, maybe you should.

11:47.139 --> 11:50.199
-Maybe I will.
-Yeah, me too.

11:50.643 --> 11:52.440
All right, what are you
gonna say to him?

11:52.611 --> 11:54.977
Just gonna find out
if he's interested.

11:55.147 --> 11:56.774
Hey, maybe I should go in with him.

11:56.949 --> 11:59.008
-No, you stay in the car.
-Who made you leader?

11:59.185 --> 12:02.677
All right, Newman. One more peep
out of you, you're out of the operation.

12:04.423 --> 12:06.948
There he is.
He's going into that bar.

12:09.195 --> 12:10.822
All right...

12:11.630 --> 12:13.723
...I'm going in.
-Be careful, Kramer.

12:17.103 --> 12:18.400
I should've gone in with him.

12:18.571 --> 12:20.630
No, you stay here in the car.
I may need you.

12:20.806 --> 12:22.330
What do you need me
in the car for?

12:22.508 --> 12:25.033
I might need you to get me a soda.

12:34.854 --> 12:37.118
I'll have a brewski, Charlie.

12:37.289 --> 12:39.154
The name's Mitch.

12:39.325 --> 12:41.987
Well, there's nothing like a cold one
after a long day, huh?

12:42.161 --> 12:43.992
-Yeah.
-Oh, yeah.

12:44.163 --> 12:47.257
Yeah, I've been known to drink
a beer or two.

12:47.500 --> 12:50.799
But then again, I've been known
to do a lot of things.

13:03.082 --> 13:04.982
-Cigarette?
-No, no. I never touch them.

13:05.384 --> 13:06.612
Well...

13:06.786 --> 13:09.880
...I suck them down like Coca-Cola.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.019
Well...

13:13.192 --> 13:16.127
...here's to feeling good
all the time, huh?

13:33.846 --> 13:37.009
Looks like you got yourself
a little cold there, huh, fella?

13:37.183 --> 13:40.209
-I don't think so.
-Me neither.

13:47.593 --> 13:50.323
You should try this new
dental floss, Glide. It's fantastic.

13:50.496 --> 13:52.726
-I use Dentotape.
-You should try this.

13:53.632 --> 13:55.896
-I don't wanna.
-Not even once?

13:56.402 --> 13:59.667
-No.
-You know, you're an idiot.

13:59.839 --> 14:01.363
Why, because I use Dentotape?

14:01.540 --> 14:05.203
Right. Anyone who uses Dentotape
is an idiot.

14:05.644 --> 14:07.407
-South America, huh?
-Yeah, yeah.

14:07.580 --> 14:08.979
That's a burgeoning continent.

14:09.148 --> 14:11.912
Well, they are expanding
their economic base, yeah.

14:12.084 --> 14:13.381
Tell me about it.

14:13.853 --> 14:15.787
Excuse me, I gotta go
to the bathroom.

14:15.955 --> 14:17.445
I'm hip.

14:19.191 --> 14:22.991
-Hip to what?
-To the whole scene.

14:23.929 --> 14:27.057
-What scene?
-The bathroom scene.

14:28.901 --> 14:31.495
Listen, don't take this personally,
but when I come back...

14:31.670 --> 14:34.901
...I'm sitting over there.
-Whatever turns you on.

14:40.112 --> 14:43.013
-No, no, I don't like it.
-What do you mean, you don't like it?

14:43.182 --> 14:46.174
-How could you not like it?
-I like the thick tape.

15:09.308 --> 15:12.471
Hey. What kind of nut are you?

15:15.381 --> 15:19.784
So basically, George,
the job here is quite simple.

15:19.952 --> 15:21.647
Selling bras.

15:21.820 --> 15:24.653
That interests me very much,
Mr. Farkus. Very much indeed, sir.

15:24.823 --> 15:26.814
Have you ever sold
a woman's line before?

15:26.992 --> 15:29.085
No, but...

15:29.261 --> 15:31.752
...I have a very good rapport
with women.

15:31.931 --> 15:33.762
Very good. Comfortable.

15:33.933 --> 15:38.131
And from the first time I laid eyes
on a brassiere...

15:38.304 --> 15:39.931
...I was enthralled.

15:42.241 --> 15:43.833
Tell me about it.

15:44.376 --> 15:46.901
Well, I was 14 years old...

15:47.079 --> 15:49.343
...I was in my friend's bathroom...

15:49.515 --> 15:53.417
...his mother's brassiere
was hanging over the shower rod.

15:53.652 --> 15:55.210
I picked it up.

15:55.387 --> 15:57.252
I studied it.

15:57.623 --> 15:59.215
I thought:

15:59.391 --> 16:00.619
"I like this."

16:00.793 --> 16:04.320
I didn't know in what way
or on what level, but I knew...

16:04.496 --> 16:06.987
...I wanted to be around brassieres.

16:07.166 --> 16:09.828
That's an incredible story.

16:10.602 --> 16:14.299
You have a remarkable passion
for brassieres.

16:14.473 --> 16:17.670
Well, they're more than just
underwear to me, Mr. Farkus.

16:18.177 --> 16:19.974
Two cups in the front...

16:20.145 --> 16:22.204
...two loops in the back...

16:22.481 --> 16:23.573
...how do they do it?

16:24.183 --> 16:26.014
Well, I think I can say...

16:26.185 --> 16:28.210
...barring some
unforeseen incident...

16:28.387 --> 16:31.686
...that you will have a very bright
future here at E.D. Granmont.

16:32.491 --> 16:35.051
Thank you, Mr. Farkus.
Thank you very much indeed, sir.

16:35.227 --> 16:36.660
See you Monday, 9:00.

16:37.296 --> 16:39.025
If you don't mind, sir...

16:39.198 --> 16:40.859
...I'll be here at 8.

16:41.200 --> 16:42.724
Excellent.

16:43.035 --> 16:45.128
So long, Mr. Farkus.

16:56.081 --> 16:58.914
-What do you think you're doing?
-Nothing. What?

16:59.084 --> 17:00.574
Farkus, get out here.

17:01.086 --> 17:03.111
Oh, yes, Ms. De Granmont?

17:03.288 --> 17:04.550
Farkus...

17:04.723 --> 17:06.917
...who is this perverted little weasel?

17:07.092 --> 17:09.753
This is Costanza,
he's our new bra salesman.

17:09.928 --> 17:11.792
He's supposed to start on Monday.

17:12.196 --> 17:14.461
If he's here on Monday, you're not.

17:14.633 --> 17:16.294
Take your pick.

17:17.269 --> 17:20.727
Get out. I'm terribly sorry,
Ms. De Granmont.

17:22.207 --> 17:24.038
You wanted to see me,
Mr. Lippman?

17:24.209 --> 17:28.509
I was just going over
the Jake Jarmel book...

17:28.680 --> 17:31.774
...and I understand you worked
with him very closely on this.

17:31.950 --> 17:34.077
Yes... Yes, I did.

17:34.253 --> 17:37.245
And anyway, I was just reading
your final edit...

17:37.423 --> 17:43.055
...and there seems to be an inordinate
number of exclamation points.

17:43.462 --> 17:49.765
Well, I... I felt that the writing lacked
a certain emotion and intensity.

17:49.935 --> 17:51.266
You know, it's...

17:51.437 --> 17:56.739
"It was a damp and chilly afternoon,
so I decided to put on my sweatshirt!"

17:57.342 --> 17:58.570
Right. Well...

17:58.744 --> 18:00.939
You put an exclamation point
after "sweatshirt."

18:01.113 --> 18:05.482
That's correct. I felt that the character
doesn't like to be chilly.

18:05.651 --> 18:06.879
I see.

18:07.052 --> 18:10.510
"I pulled the lever on the machine,
but the Clark bar didn't come out!"

18:11.356 --> 18:13.153
-Again, exclamation point.
-Yeah.

18:13.325 --> 18:15.316
Well, you know how frustrating
that can be...

18:15.494 --> 18:18.327
...when you keep putting quarters
and quarters into a machine...

18:18.497 --> 18:21.933
...and... nothing comes out.
-Get rid of the exclamation points.

18:22.101 --> 18:23.966
-Okay, I will.
-I hate exclamation points.

18:24.136 --> 18:25.660
Okay.

18:26.738 --> 18:28.706
Just... I'll...

18:30.075 --> 18:31.736
"Dear Barry, consider this letter...

18:31.910 --> 18:34.777
...the termination of our relationship,
effective immediately."

18:34.947 --> 18:36.812
-Exclamation point.
-Right.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.812
You still have no proof.

18:39.985 --> 18:42.112
Elaine, he was sniffing like crazy
around me.

18:42.287 --> 18:44.949
"I will expect all funds in the form
of a cashier's check...

18:45.124 --> 18:46.614
...no later than the 18th."

18:46.792 --> 18:49.192
Double exclamation point.

18:49.995 --> 18:51.690
-Will that take care of ours too?
-Yep.

18:51.864 --> 18:54.196
I'll give you yours as soon as
I get my money back.

18:54.366 --> 18:56.061
Want me to mail it?
I'm on my way out.

18:56.235 --> 18:59.636
-Yeah, thanks.
-All right. Be my pleasure.

19:03.775 --> 19:05.709
See you later.

19:06.512 --> 19:08.377
You know, this is...

19:09.481 --> 19:11.574
-Hey, Ralph.
-What's up, fellas?

19:11.750 --> 19:13.650
-That'll be 14.30.
-All right.

19:13.819 --> 19:16.515
-Mushrooms? You got mushrooms.
-Yeah.

19:17.456 --> 19:20.289
-What's the matter, you got a cold?
-No, man.

19:20.459 --> 19:22.984
-Kramer, what is this?
-It's a sweater.

19:23.162 --> 19:25.926
-What is it made out of?
-I don't know. Jerry gave it to me.

19:26.098 --> 19:28.566
-It's mohair, I think.
-Mohair. That figures.

19:28.734 --> 19:30.361
I'm allergic to mohair.

19:30.536 --> 19:32.902
-You mean, you just started sniffing?
-Yeah.

19:33.071 --> 19:34.698
Mohair does it to me every time.

19:36.542 --> 19:39.443
I was wearing that sweater in the
coffee shop when Barry came in.

19:39.611 --> 19:43.570
-Jerry, I was wearing it in the bar.
-The sweater made him sniff.

19:43.749 --> 19:46.240
See? I told you he wasn't
a drug addict.

19:46.418 --> 19:47.646
Oh, no, the letter.

19:47.819 --> 19:51.118
Newman... It's got
exclamation points all over it.

19:51.290 --> 19:54.191
Not to mention the picture of him
on the toilet.

19:58.363 --> 19:59.694
The what?

20:10.275 --> 20:12.539
-After you.
-Thank you.

20:14.780 --> 20:16.543
Get your hands off of me!

20:16.848 --> 20:19.544
Johnny! Johnny!

20:24.990 --> 20:26.821
What do you mean,
you felt her material?

20:26.992 --> 20:28.550
What? With your fingers, like this?

20:28.727 --> 20:30.957
So what? What's so bad about that?

20:31.129 --> 20:33.791
Who goes around
feeling people's material?

20:33.966 --> 20:37.458
What can be gained
by feeling a person's material?

20:37.636 --> 20:38.967
It's insanity.

20:39.137 --> 20:41.901
Whatever happened to, "My,
that's a lovely dress you have on.

20:42.074 --> 20:43.336
May I have this dance?"

20:49.681 --> 20:53.117
You know, you are really lucky
Newman never mailed that letter.

20:53.919 --> 20:56.945
Sorry I'm late. I just came from
a meeting with my lawyer.

20:57.122 --> 20:58.680
-Hey.
-What is this?

20:58.857 --> 21:02.623
It's a letter from your friend
Barry Prophet's lawyer.

21:03.528 --> 21:05.587
He's filing Chapter 11?

21:05.764 --> 21:07.857
What's going on?
Why is he filing Chapter 11?

21:08.033 --> 21:09.364
Bankruptcy.

21:09.534 --> 21:12.526
Bankruptcy. As in, "I've taken
your money and spent it on drugs."

21:13.472 --> 21:15.303
What? I thought it was the sweater.

21:15.474 --> 21:17.499
-What about the money?
-What about the money?

21:17.676 --> 21:19.735
If I had dissolved my relationship
with him...

21:19.911 --> 21:22.937
...prior to his filing Chapter 11,
I could've got the money back.

21:23.115 --> 21:24.343
Which I would've done...

21:24.516 --> 21:28.509
...if a certain imbecile had been able
to get to a mailbox and mail a letter.

21:34.393 --> 21:36.327
Pair of bear claws, please.

21:42.968 --> 21:44.458
Nice.

21:44.636 --> 21:46.536
-Think so?
-Yeah, what is it?

21:46.905 --> 21:48.839
Half silk, half cotton, half linen.

21:51.076 --> 21:53.237
How can you go wrong?

22:01.553 --> 22:04.044
My accountant actually did...

22:04.222 --> 22:07.487
...take a big chunk of money from me
and use it to buy drugs.

22:07.659 --> 22:10.389
The thing that was hardest for me
to comprehend about this...

22:10.562 --> 22:15.056
...is the life choice of drug abuse
and accounting.

22:16.201 --> 22:18.863
It makes sense. Why would
an athlete or musician take drugs?

22:19.037 --> 22:20.402
They have an interesting job.

22:20.572 --> 22:24.201
But an accountant? If ever a job
required hallucinogenic support...

22:24.376 --> 22:26.105
...this is the job.

22:26.278 --> 22:28.576
That should be the legal defense.

22:28.747 --> 22:31.443
"You're charged with
possession of illegal narcotics."

22:31.616 --> 22:34.551
"But, Your Honor,
I'm an accountant."

22:35.287 --> 22:36.515
Bang. "Case closed.

22:36.688 --> 22:40.180
Bailiff, give this man his peyote
and tequila back for the drive home.

22:40.359 --> 22:42.793
Sorry to bother you, sir.
Terribly sorry."

